<li><cite data-id="B18FF3E3-E506-4883-9F81-C4BB74B32E80">Spear</cite> by Nicola Griffith</li>
<li><cite data-id="917E003D-D50C-4F24-9D1D-D1A92C88C69E">The Three Musketeers</cite> by Alexander Dumas (translated by Lawrence Ellsworth)</li>
<li><cite data-id="FB27689F-EFB6-4C17-A9B9-D4759FC2572F">Why Orwell Matters</cite> by Christopher Hitchens</li>
</ul>
<p>I abandoned the following books:</p>
<ul>
<li><cite data-id="37F1A94E-E29E-4745-8C05-FD507311E2C9">The Mists of Avalon</cite> by Marion Zimmer Bradley</li>
<li><cite data-id="81AAA17D-763D-47BD-9924-C06ED85214C3">Le Morte d’Arthur</cite> by Thomas Mallory</li>
</ul>
<p>I started and continue to work through:</p>
<ul>
<li><cite data-id="6974688C-4EAC-45E3-A5DF-CC3AAB2AB744"><a href="https://search.worldcat.org/title/1330933372">Active Hope</a></cite> by Joanna Macy and Chris Johnstone</li>
<li><cite data-id="60AC3AEC-35C9-4E95-806F-FDF6A35573E0">On Anarchism</cite> by Noam Chomsky</li>
<li><cite data-id="55348AB8-9909-4E68-878A-5458701F87E1">Freedom is a Constant Struggle</cite> by Angela Y. Davis</li>
<li><cite data-id="40F8F0C5-9BB2-4424-A371-656FCA0B58C2">Letters to Olga</cite> by Václav Havel</li>
<li><cite data-id="C5494904-CE49-4456-8E29-E3F94B72A593">The Life of Poetry</cite> by Muriel Rukeyser</li>
<li><cite data-id="A6B3DC34-C462-46BC-8CD7-D89BDC31D6EB">The Once and Future King</cite> by T.H. White</li>
<li><cite data-id="80CDB491-FFFE-4F27-A901-8E84A97415E6">Patriot</cite> by Alexei Navalny</li>
<li><cite data-id="0D14E25B-DD86-445E-BD3F-AAE165774566">Worlds of Arthur</cite> by Guy Halsall</li>
