<p>One thing I’m falling further in love with is a book’s introduction. Timothy
Snyder’s introduction in <cite data-id="26A608F1-70C2-4E23-9DA0-B2C978D5BB52">The Power of the Powerless</cite> laid excellent ground work
to help me receive Václav Havel’s writing; whom I (re-)learned about in <cite data-id="FB27689F-EFB6-4C17-A9B9-D4759FC2572F">Why Orwell Matters</cite>; a book that I think will be amongst my most important reads.</p>
<h2 id="writing">Writing</h2>
<p><a href="https://takeonrules.com/2024/">My Posts for 2024</a> summarizes the “stats” for the year. I’m proud of the 12
<a href="https://takeonrules.com/tags/poetry">poetry posts I wrote</a>. I definitely did not keep up with the <span><a href="https://spriggans-den.com/2023/12/10/lore-24/">Lore24</a></span> <small><a class="ref" rel="tag opener" aria-label="Other site-wide references of “Lore24”" title="Other site-wide references of “Lore24”" href="https://takeonrules.com/site-map/glossary/#abbr-dfn-LORE24">&#128214;</a></small>
challenge.</p>
<p>And I’m finding that with my practice of regular writing, I’m able to write
posts in less time. The quick ones are those where I write about extending
<span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emacs">Emacs</a></span> <small><a class="ref" rel="tag opener" aria-label="Other site-wide references of “Emacs”" title="Other site-wide references of “Emacs”" href="https://takeonrules.com/site-map/glossary/#abbr-dfn-EMACS">&#128214;</a></small>
. I’ve done the work so I use writing as my time to both synthesize and
share that work.</p>
<p>But I’m also finding other posts flow a bit smoother. I suspect some of this
comes from being more deliberate with my attention. I deleted my Facebook
account. I continue to run aggressive ad-blocking in my browser; or favor the
text based browser to minimize distractions.</p>
<p>I have also established a strong separation between my work and personal life.
Namely when I’m wrapping up at work, I close my work laptop and write on paper
my tasks for the next day. That ritual of writing ensures that I’m not
ruminating on those software tasks during my evening hours.</p>
<h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2>
<p>Aside from aiming for 90 minutes of reading a day, I’m not going to commit to
any challenges or resolutions for <time datetime="2024" title="2024">2025</time>. I will however, continue to work to
learn and grow my empathy and community.</p>
